Domain: a burglary investigation. Evidence atom E: Fingerprint(suspect_S, window_frame_W, time_T). Background facts (assumed or independently established): BG1 OwnsHouse(victim_V, house_H); BG2 ContainsWindow(H, W); BG3 PointOfEntry(W, burglary_B); BG4 ¬AuthorizedVisitor(S, H, [T−30d, T]); BG5 FingerprintsPersistAtMost(W, 30d). Rule R (defeasible): ∀x,y,t. Fingerprint(x,y,t) ∧ ¬AuthorizedVisitor(x, owner(y), [t−persistence(y), t]) ⇒ Touched(x, y, t' ) for some t' ∈ [t−persistence(y), t]. Inference step (modus ponens under R, with BG4 discharging the negative condition and BG5 bounding persistence): from E, BG2, BG4, BG5 conclude C1: Touched(S, W, t') for some t' ∈ [T−30d, T]. Second step (abductive, defeasible) using BG1–BG3: best explanation of C1 conjoined with PointOfEntry(W, B) is Present(S, at W, during B), yielding conclusion C2: Present(S, W, time(B)) with confidence weighted by the prior of alternative explanations (e.g., legitimate prior contact). Defeaters to record explicitly: D1 evidence of lawful prior access (would defeat BG4); D2 contamination of W after B (would defeat the temporal binding); D3 fingerprint-transfer artifact (would defeat the Touched→Present link). Formal status: C2 is a defeasible conclusion of strength s = P(C2 | E, BG, ¬D1 ∧ ¬D2 ∧ ¬D3), to be revised if any Dᵢ is later supported.
